026/5/3/baseball-west-virginia-completes-sweep-of-kansas-state</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Armani Guzman celebrates after a base hit against Kansas State" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260502_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-08185.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 18 West Virginia University baseball team completed a sweep of Kansas State with a 13-6 win on Sunday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 31-12 and 16-8 in the Big 12 while the Wildcats fall to 26-22 and 9-15 in league play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260502_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-08185.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260502_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-08185.jpg"><media:title>Armani Guzman celebrates after a base hit against Kansas State</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260502_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-08185.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 3 May 2026 19:05:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59074</s:story_id></item><item><title>McDonald Earns Runner-Up Finish at East Coast Relays</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/3/track-field-mcdonald-earns-runner-up-finish-at-east-coast-relays</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/3/track-field-mcdonald-earns-runner-up-finish-at-east-coast-relays</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Lily Haught" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260417_TRACK_MountaineerShowcase_TT_4818.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University track and field team wrapped up competition at the East Coast Relays over the weekend.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260417_TRACK_MountaineerShowcase_TT_4818.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260417_TRACK_MountaineerShowcase_TT_4818.jpg"><media:title>Lily Haught</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260417_TRACK_MountaineerShowcase_TT_4818.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 3 May 2026 15:18:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59073</s:story_id></item><item><title>Cole Tosses Gem Against Kansas State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/2/baseball-cole-tosses-gem-against-kansas-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/2/baseball-cole-tosses-gem-against-kansas-state</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Chansen Cole throws a pitch against the Kansas State Wildcats" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/2/20260421_BASE_WVUvsPitt_TT-00352.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 18 West Virginia University baseball team defeated Kansas State, 9-1, Saturday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark as sophomore Chansen Cole tossed a complete game. The Mountaineers improve to 30-12 and 15-8 in the Big 12 while the Wildcats fall to 26-21 and 9-14 in league play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/2/20260421_BASE_WVUvsPitt_TT-00352.jpg" /><media:conten